Wertheimer Whiplash, Trump Blame Games, Lemon=E2=80=99s Media Wars

Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon dose of Puck=E2=80=99s be=
st new reporting.

First up today, Peter Hamby delivers an essential, thirteenth-hour snapshot=
 of the most pressing Election Day plotlines, bellwethers, and the potentia=
l surprises that insiders are tracking: Which East Coast counties will fore=
shadow how on-the-fence, battleground state voters will break? Is Gen Z act=
ually going to show up? How will the polling averages shake out against the=
 actual results? All that, and much, much more=E2=80=A6

Plus, below the fold: Lauren Sherman digs into the restructuring at Chanel =
as the luxury business homes in on a new creative director. Scott Mendelson=
 reveals the one weird Hollywood trick for making money on a mid-sized glob=
al hit. On Somebody=E2=80=99s Gotta Win, Tara Palmeri rings up Axios=E2=80=
=99s Alex Thompson to preview the post-Election Night blame game. On Impoli=
tic, John
Heilemann and MSNBC=E2=80=99s Nicolle Wallace chew over Harris=E2=80=99s cl=
osing argument and that bolt-from-the-blue Iowa poll that stunned the polit=
ical world. On The Grill Room, Dylan Byers kicks back with Don Lemon to tra=
de media war stories and peel back the curtain on the ex-CNN anchor=E2=80=
=99s meteoric rise. And on The Powers That Be, Abby Livingston drops in to =
answer the final questions haunting this interminable presidential race.

